title: Troll Talking Interceptor (ADR-228 Phase 5)
story: dungeo
description: Regression test for the live bug where TrollTalkingInterceptor (MDL "Unfortunately, the troll can't hear you.") was registered on if.action.talking but never fired because talking was unwired. The conscious-troll passthrough is unit-covered (talking-interceptor.test.ts); this transcript minimizes live-troll exposure to dodge combat RNG.

---

# Setup — lantern, teleport, and KO the troll all in one GDT session
# (the troll attacks every turn we spend in his room while conscious)
> GDT
[OK: contains "GDT"]

> TK brass lantern
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> AH Troll Room
[OK: contains "Teleported"]

> KO troll
[OK: contains "Knocked out"]

> EX
[OK: contains "Returning"]

> turn on lantern
[OK: contains "on"]

# ============================================================
# The dead-registration fix: "speak to troll" routes through
# stdlib if.action.talking, where the newly-wired
# TrollTalkingInterceptor vetoes with the MDL canon line
# ============================================================

> speak to troll
[OK: contains "can't hear you"]

# The story action's literal phrasing still works too
> talk to troll
[OK: contains "can't hear you"]
